Title : Santo Tagliafico
Text : '''Santo Tagliafico''', also known as '''Santino Fortunato Tagliafichi''', (1756 - 1829) was an [[Italy|Italian]] painter, mainly active in [[Genoa]]. He trained under [[Carlo Giuseppe Ratti]]. He was a member of a prolific family of artists, including father, Nicol√≤ Gaetano (1698-1776) (engineer and scenic designer), and Santo's brothers starting with Andrea (architect); Giuseppe (priest and not artist); Giovanni (architect); Giambattista (engineer and scenic designer); and Domenico (jeweller). Further family members were (Emanuele) Andrea (1729-1812), and Giovanni Andrea.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=aOGhAAAAMAAJ Notizie dei professori del disegno in Liguria dalla fondazione dell' Accademia], Volume 1. (1865), by Federigo Alizeri, Publisher Luigi Sambolini, Genoa, pages 379-390.</ref> One of Santo's pupils was [[Gaetano Gallino]].<ref>[http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/gaetano-gallino_(Dizionario-Biografico)/ Treccani Encyclopedia], entry by Roberto Massetti, Dizionario Biografico degli Italiani - Volume 51 (1998).</ref>

